description:
A library that can easily provide threaded execution of SQL statements and commands. It can be used to expose an interface to Microsoft Excel clients, providing threaded, async operations to a single-thread application.

Examples:

Simplifies SQL execution, encapsulating construction, execution, and destruction of SQL elements. 

Usage: 

ISqlCommandParameters param = new SqlCommandParameters(); 
 param.CommandTimeOut = 60; 
 param.DatabaseName = "%db name%"; 
 param.SqlServerInstance = @"%server name%"; 
 param.StoredProcedure = "SELECT * FROM %table%"; 

 ISqlCommandExecution exec = new SqlCommandExecution(param); 

 exec.Execute(); 
 System.Data.DataSet set = exec.Data; 
 int rowCount = set.Tables[0].Rows.Count; 

 exec.Dispose(); 

Alt Usage (with Using): 

using (ISqlCommandExecution execUsing = new SqlCommandExecution(new SqlCommandParameters() 
 { 
 CommandTimeOut = 60, 
 DatabaseName = "%db name%", 
 SqlServerInstance = @"%server name%", 
 StoredProcedure = "SELECT * FROM %table%" 
 })) 
 { 
 execUsing.Execute(); 
 System.Data.DataSet setUsing = execUsing.Data; 
 //verify it works 
 return setUsing.Tables[0].Rows.Count; 
}
